    "body": "### Steps to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ spack  install  intel@19.0.4\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Platform and user environment\r\n\r\nCurrent SPACK (devel) from today (cfbdd21)\r\n```\r\nLinux login 3.10.0-957.12.2.el7.x86_64 #1 SMP Tue May 14 21:24:32 UTC 2019 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\nCentOS Linux release 7.6.1810\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\nThe Intel compiler got installed into .../opt/linux-centos7-**broadwell**/gcc-.../intel-19.0.4-...\r\nAs the Intel compiler is just a binary blob I do not see any use of putting it into a directory of a specific architecture instead of linux-centos7-**x86_64**",
